Crush 40 wafers; mix with 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine. Press onto bottom of 13x9-inch pan; set aside. Beat pudding mixes and milk in large bowl with whisk 2 minutes. Stir in COOL WHIP; spread 1/2 onto crust. Cover with layers of remaining wafers and pudding mixture. Refrigerate 3 hours. Meanwhile, toss strawberries with remaining sugar. Refrigerate until ready to use. Cut dessert into squares to serve; top each with about 2 Tbsp. berry mixture.